285 g Top Sirloin Steak
2 unit(s) Purple Sweet Potato
113 g Mushrooms
113 g Baby Tomatoes
1 unit(s) Shallot
7 g Parsley
¼ cup Goat Cheese, crumbled
28 g Pepitas
10 g Gravy Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
4 g Garlic Salt
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Prick tomatoes with a fork.
Peel, then cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes and 1/2 tbsp oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with pepper and half the garlic salt. Toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 8-9 min. Flip and return to oven for 8-9 min, until potatoes are tender and golden. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast in the top and middle of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Meanwhile, thinly slice mushrooms.
Finely chop parsley.
Finely chop shallot.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
When hot, add pepitas to the dry pan. Toast for 4-5 min, stirring often, until golden. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)
Remove from heat. Transfer to a plate.

Pat steak dry with paper towels. Season with pepper and remaining garlic salt.
Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then steak. Cook 1-2 min per side, until browned.
Remove from heat and transfer to an unlined baking sheet.

On one half of the baking sheet, arrange steak. On the other half, arrange tomatoes. Roast steak and tomatoes in the bottom of the oven for 5-8 min, or until cooked to desired doneness.**
When done, remove from heat.
Transfer steak to a cutting board. Loosely cover with foil and set aside to rest for 2-3 min.
Keep tomatoes on the baking sheet. Set aside.

In the same pan (from step 3), heat 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil over medium.
When hot, add mushrooms. Cook for 2 min, stirring often, until beginning to soften. Season with salt.
Add shallots. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring often, until softened.
Sprinkle half the Gravy Spice Blend (use all for 4 servings) over top. Cook for 30 sec, until coated.
Add broth concentrate and 1/2 cup water (1 cup) water. Bring to a gentle boil. Once boiling, cook for 2-3 min, stirring often, until gravy thickens. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.

Thinly slice steak.
Stir any steak resting juices into gravy.
Divide potatoes, tomatoes and steak between plates.
Top potatoes and tomatoes with pepitas, goat cheese and parsley.
Spoon mushroom gravy over top of steak.